definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate + lipoamide -eq- S-(2-methylpropanoyl)dihydrolipoamide + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate -eq- tetrahydrofolate + 2-dehydropantoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a 3-oxo-5-alpha-steroid + acceptor -eq- a 3-oxo-delta(4)-steroid + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phosphoshikimate + phosphoenolpyruvate -eq- 5-O-(1-carboxyvinyl)-3-phosphoshikimate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-aminobutanoate + amino group acceptor -eq- succinate semialdehyde + amino acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate + O2 -eq- homogentisate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  glycine + H(+) + succinyl-CoA -eq- 5-aminolevulinate + CO(2) + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-methyltetrahydropteroyltri-L-glutamate + L-homocysteine -eq- L-methionine + tetrahydropteroyltri-L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-fructose-6-phosphate -eq- ADP + D-fructose 1,6-bisphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-fructose 6-phosphate + ATP -eq- beta-D-fructose 2,6-bisphosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  7,8-dihydroneopterin 3'-triphosphate -eq- 6-pyruvoyl-5,6,7,8-tetrahydropterin + H(+) + triphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N2-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-arginine + H2O -eq- L-arginine + ADP-ribose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  AMP + H2O -eq- IMP + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ADP + ATP -eq- phosphate + P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-adenosyl)tetraphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + ADP + H(+) + oxaloacetate + phosphate -eq- ATP + citrate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)-ATP + diphosphate -eq- ATP + 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group to the oxygen atom of a carboxyl group at the C-terminal of a protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  myo-inositol + CDP-diacylglycerol -eq- 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol + CMP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  CDP-diacylglycerol + L-serine -eq- CMP + O-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + UTP + NH3 -eq- ADP + phosphate + CTP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a D-amino acid + H2O + O2 -eq- a 2-oxo acid + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-arabinono-1,4-lactone + O(2) -eq- dehydro-D-arabinono-1,4-lactone + H(2)O(2) + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + DNA containing cytosine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + DNA containing 5-methylcytosine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + DNA(n+1) -  the synthesis of DNA from deoxyribonucleotide triphosphates in the presence of a DNA template and a 3'hydroxyl group.

Catalysis of the synthesis of a short RNA primer on a DNA template, providing a free 3'-OH that can be extended by DNA-directed DNA polymerases. Catalyzed by a DNA-directed RNA polymerase that forms a complex with alpha DNA polymerase.

Catalysis of the reaction -  nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + RNA(n+1). Utilizes a DNA template, i.e. the catalysis of DNA-template-directed extension of the 3'-end of an RNA strand by one nucleotide at a time. Can initiate a chain 'de novo'.
Catalysis of the reaction -  cyclobutadipyrimidine (in DNA) -eq- 2 pyrimidine residues (in DNA). This reaction represents the reactivation of irradiated DNA by light.

Catalysis of the reaction -  DNA with alkylated base + H2O -eq- DNA with abasic site + alkylated base. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar to remove an alkylated base, leaving an apyrimidinic or apurinic site.

label.value: DNA-(apurinic or apyrimidinic site) lyase activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the cleavage of the C-O-P bond 3' to the apurinic or apyrimidinic site in DNA by a beta-elimination reaction, leaving a 3'-terminal unsaturated sugar and a product with a terminal 5'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  DNA (containing 6-O-methylguanine) + (protein)-L-cysteine -eq- DNA (without 6-O-methylguanine) + protein S-methyl-L-cysteine.

Catalysis of the formation of a phosphodiester bond between the 3'-hydroxyl group at the end of one DNA chain and the 5'-phosphate group at the end of another. This reaction requires an energy source such as ATP or NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + deoxyribonucleotide(n) + deoxyribonucleotide(m) -eq- AMP + diphosphate + deoxyribonucleotide(n+m).
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD+ + deoxyribonucleotide(n) + deoxyribonucleotide(m) -eq- AMP + nicotinamide nucleotide + deoxyribonucleotide(n+m).
Catalysis of the reaction -  deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + DNA(n+1).
Catalysis of the repair of a photoproduct resulting from ultraviolet irradiation of two adjacent pyrimidine residues in DNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pyrimidine-pyrimidone (6-4) photoproduct (in DNA) -eq- 2 pyrimidine residues (in DNA). Catalyzes the reactivation of ultraviolet-irradiated DNA.
Catalysis of the transient cleavage and passage of individual DNA strands or double helices through one another, resulting a topological transformation in double-stranded DNA.
Catalysis of a DNA topological transformation by transiently cleaving one DNA strand at a time to allow passage of another strand -  changes the linking number by +1 per catalytic cycle.

Catalysis of a DNA topological transformation by transiently cleaving a pair of complementary DNA strands to form a gate through which a second double-stranded DNA segment is passed, after which the severed strands in the first DNA segment are rejoined -  product release is coupled to ATP binding and hydrolysis -  changes the linking number in multiples of 2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + FMN -eq- diphosphate + FAD.
Catalysis of the reaction -  IMP + NADP(+) + NH(4)(+) -eq- GMP + 2 H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + xanthosine 5'-phosphate + NH3 -eq- AMP + diphosphate + GMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + xanthosine 5'-phosphate + L-glutamine + H2O -eq- AMP + diphosphate + GMP + L-glutamate.

Catalysis of the formation of the linkage between a protein and a glycosylphosphatidylinositol anchor. The reaction probably occurs by subjecting a peptide bond to nucleophilic attack by the amino group of ethanolamine-GPI, transferring the protein from a signal peptide to the GPI anchor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + H2O -eq- GDP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the imidazole ring of GTP, releasing formate. Two C-N bonds are hydrolyzed and the pentase unit is isomerized.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + H2O -eq- formate + 7,8-dihydroneopterin 3'-triphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + 3 H(2)O -eq- 2,5-diamino-6-hydroxy-4-(5-phosphoribosylamino)-pyrimidine + diphosphate + formate + 3 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  IMP + H2O -eq- 5-formamido-1-(5-phosphoribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  inosine 5'-phosphate + NAD+ + H2O -eq- xanthosine 5'-phosphate + NADH + H+.
